LINUX
- man <command> - documentation
- echo "..." - returns text we provide
- whoami - returns user we're logged in as
- ls - listings folders
- ls -a - listing all folders
- ls -help - help with ls
- cd - change directory
- cat - content of file
- pwd - shows full path to directory
- find -name <file/*> - finds path to file
- grep "81.143.211.90" access.log - searchs for that in acces log file
- grep -R "PRETTY_NAME" /etc/ - searches for that in whole directory
- & - makes sth in the background
- com1 && com2 - command2 will be done after com1
- echo hey > welcome - message hey in file welcome
- echo hello >> welcome - adds hello at the end


FILES:
- touch - create file
- mkdir - create folder
- cp - copy file/folder
- mv - move file/folder
- rm - remove file/folder
- file - type of file

RIGHTS:
- ls -lh - permissions, owner
  Owner/group/others - 3/3/3
- read 4
- write 2
- execute 1

DIRECTORIES:
- /etc - store system files
- /var - store data frequently accessed
- /root - home for root system user 
- /tmp - store data needed only once/twice

EDITING:
- nano <file> - editing a file
- wget <http.adress> - downloading file
- scp - transfer from local host - scp important.txt (what we import) ubuntu@192.168.1.30:/home/ubuntu/transferred.txt (as what we import)

